\left(\begin{array}{c} 4\\ 2\\ r\\ \end{array}\right)=\alpha\left(\begin{array}{c} 1\\ 2\\ 3\\ \end{array}\right)+\beta\left(\begin{array}{c} 1\\ 1\\ 1\\ \end{array}\right)\Leftrightarrow\left(\begin{array}{c} 4\\ 2\\ r\\ \end{array}\right)=\left(\begin{array}{c} \alpha+\beta\\ 2\alpha+\beta\\ 3\alpha+\beta\\ \end{array}\right)\Rightarrow\left\{ \begin{array}{c} 4=\alpha+\beta\\  2=2\alpha+\beta\\ r=3\alpha+\beta\\ \end{array}\right.
